      {
        "content": "SWC-115: Authorization through tx.origin\n\ntx.origin should not be used for authorization. A malicious contract called by the authorized account can forward the call and pass a tx.origin check. Remediation: use msg.sender for authorization.",
        "doc_id": "SWC-115",
        "chunk_id": 0,
        "total_chunks": 1,
        "metadata": {
          "protocol": "unknown",
          "date": "2020-01-01",
          "vuln_type": "transaction_order_dependence",
          "severity": "medium",
          "loss_usd": 0,
          "chain": "",
          "url": "https://swcregistry.io/docs/SWC-115",
          "source": "swc_registry",
          "chunk_id": 0,
          "total_chunks": 1,
          "doc_id": "SWC-115"
        },
        "score": 0.03306010928961749
      },
      {
        "content": "Authorization via tx.origin enables phishing relay\n\nrequire(tx.origin == owner) lets a malicious intermediary contract act on the owner's behalf when the owner calls it, since tx.origin remains the owner. Fix: authenticate with msg.sender, never tx.origin.",
        "doc_id": "solodit-tx-origin-auth",
        "chunk_id": 0,
        "total_chunks": 1,
        "metadata": {
          "protocol": "Wallet",
